   "narrative": "Deacon Josiah Rogers died in December 1792 in the 28th year of his age, as recorded on his stone at Elmwood Cemetery. His wife Sarah died in September 1779 at Waterbury, Connecticut. A veteran marker indicates military service connected to this grave. Born around 1764 and dying at 28, Rogers was of the generation that came of age during the Revolutionary War; if the veteran connection is to Rogers himself, he would have been a young soldier or militia member during the final years of the conflict. The specific nature of his service has not yet been confirmed from available records. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
