   "narrative": "John Montgomery — listed on his marker as Jno. Montgomery — served in Company C of the 25th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry during the Civil War. The 25th New Jersey was organized in the fall of 1862 as a nine-month regiment, serving in the defenses around Washington before moving into Virginia and Maryland operations. Montgomery's burial in Holyoke suggests he settled in the Connecticut River Valley after the war, as many veterans did, drawn by the growing mill economy of the Pioneer Valley. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
