   "narrative": "Otto Ernest Riedel served as a Private in the United States Army during World War II. Born in 1911 and 30 years old at the time of Pearl Harbor, Riedel served within the broad mobilization that expanded the Army from fewer than 200,000 men in 1939 to more than eight million by 1945. Army Privates formed the essential foundation of that force, serving in every theater from North Africa to the Pacific. Riedel is buried in the Hupfer family plot at Elmwood Cemetery and died in 1985. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
