   "narrative": "Alfred B. Sefton served as a Staff Sergeant in the United States Army. Born January 26, 1919, Sefton was 22 years old when the United States entered World War II in December 1941. Staff Sergeants served as non-commissioned officers leading rifle squads and weapons teams, typically in direct combat or close support roles. The rank carried significant responsibility: a Staff Sergeant was expected to keep his soldiers alive, maintain unit cohesion under fire, and execute orders when officers were not present. Sefton died September 19, 1999. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
