   "narrative": "Frank H. Wade was born in 1872 and died in 1952. An American flag marks his grave at Elmwood Cemetery, indicating veteran status. Born in 1872, Wade was 25 years old during the Spanish-American War of 1898 and 44 years old when the United States entered World War I in 1917, making Spanish-American War service the most likely era for his military service. Massachusetts contributed thousands of volunteers to the Spanish-American War, many of whom served in Cuba, Puerto Rico, and the Philippines. His branch of service and unit assignment have not yet been confirmed from available records. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
